http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Visakhapatnam/Apprenticeship-interviews-for-engg.-students-on-Feb.-5/article14019196.ece

The Commissionerate of Technical Educationand Board of Apprenticeship Training (Southern Region), Chennai, will jointly hold interview sessions for engineering graduates and diploma holders for apprenticeship at Vignan Institute of Information and Technology, near VSEZ, Duvvada, on February 5.The interview is being held for apprenticeship in various private, government and PSUs, and is open for students from various streams such as electrical, electronics, mechanical, civil, metallurgy, automobile, chemical, mining, electronics and communications, instrumentation, computer science, information technology and DCCP. The interview will be held from 9.30 a.m. at the college.Students who have completed their degrees or diplomas by April 2013 are eligible to apply. Candidates should enrol their names in the national web portal:www.mhrdnats.gov.inand get user ids and passwords and bring the same to the interview along with academic original certificates for verification and three sets of photocopies of provisional certificates and bio-data.Selected will undergo one-year apprentice under the apprenticeship training scheme of Board of Apprenticeship Training , and will be paid a minimum stipend of Rs. 4,984 per month. For details visit:www.boatsr-apprentice.tn.nic.in